    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1917-02-20T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1917-02-20T00:00:00-05:00" n="349"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d349">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">818.00/107½</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">President <persName type="from">Wilson</persName> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1917-02-20">
                            <hi rend="italic">20 February, 1917</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">My Dear Mr. Secretary</hi>: I am glad you had this talk
                    with the ex-President and formed a favourable impression of him. His explanation
                    of the revolt is just what had formed in my own mind out of such information as
                    had reached us.</p>
                <p>I will be willing to see him, of course, as you request. It will add nothing to
                    what we already know, but it may make an impression in certain quarters which it
                    is desirable to make.</p>
                <p>Faithfully Yours,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>W. W.</signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
